The issue is that when `verificationMode` is not null but the condition in the inner `if` is false (i.e., when verificationMode is not MockAwareVerificationMode OR when the mocks don't match), the code falls through without re-adding the verification mode back to the mocking progress. This causes the verification mode to be lost.

